doctype html
html
	head
		meta(charset='utf-8')
		meta(content='IE=edge', http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible')
		title toolery.me
		meta(content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1', name='viewport')
		link(href='http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Code+Pro:400,300', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
		link(href='css/app.css', rel='stylesheet')

	body
		.container
			.color
				.error
				input.colorinput(type="text", name="rgbinput", id="rgbinput", placeholder="Paste a value here.")
			.other
				.opposite
				.sass
				.color-list
				.message
				.contrast-example The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog.
				.char-count
				.keypress key:
					span.keypress-code
				.units units:
					span.units-code

			a.info-toggle(href="#") info
			.information
				section
					p Everyday I need to make lots of little conversions and calculations when taking designs from Photoshop files to the web.
					p This is a little tool I made to make all of that easier for myself (and perhaps others).
					p If you think of anything it needs, get at me on twitter - #[a(href="http://twitter.com/jonnyscholes") @jonnyscholes]
				section
					p Color variable names come from #[a(href="http://chir.ag/projects/ntc/") namethatcolor.js by Chirag Mehta]
					p The WCAG check is AAA compliant (AA etc coming soon) and it currently supports finding colors in the following formats:
					ul
						li RGB - rgb(0, 0, 0)
						li RGBA - rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)
						li HEX - #000000
						li Adobe #1 - R:0 G:0 B:0
						li Adobe #2 - (R0 / G0 / B0)
					p It supports converting the following units from/to eachother (where possible):
					ul
						li rem
						li in (inches)
						li cm (centimeters)
						li pc (picas)
						li mm (milimeters)
						li pt (points)
						li px (pixels)
						li deg (degrees)
						li rad (radians)
						li s (seconds)
						li ms (miliseconds)

